  "texts": [
    "We begin with the implication from 2 to 1.",
    "Assume that X ⊆ S satisfies persistence and refinability.To show that ■ i X satisfies persistence, suppose x ′ ⊑ x and x ′ ̸ ∈ ■ i X, so there is a y ′ such that x ′ R i y ′ and y ′ ̸ ∈ X.",
    "Then since X satisfies refinability, there is a z ⊑ y ′ such that (i) for all z ′ ⊑ z, z ′ ̸ ∈ X.",
    "Since z ⊑ y ′ gives us y ′ ≬ z, from x ′ R i y ′ and R-rule we have a y such that xR i y ≬ z.",
    "Then from y ≬ z, (i), and persistence for X, it follows that y ̸ ∈ X, which with xR i y implies x ̸ ∈ ■ i X."
  ],
